  • Method Details

    • withChannel

      public static ItemStack withChannel(ItemStack masterStack, String channel)
      Return a trigger item that
      • Still carry all the subchannel in some unspecified ways
      • Have its master channel data replaced with specified subchannel's data
      If given subchannel does not exist, masterStack may or may not be returned to save performance. Code within StructureLib can depend on this behavior, you cannot.
      Parameters:
      masterStack - trigger item. can be the return value of another withChannel(ItemStack, String) call
      channel - subchannel to use. will use current master channel data instead if this channel does not exist Note: all channel identifiers are supposed to be lower case and not empty.
      Returns:
      a trigger item with new master channel

      Returns:

    • iterateChannelData

      public static Stream<Map.Entry<String,Integer>> iterateChannelData(ItemStack masterStack)
      Iterate over all subchannel data on trigger stack. Does not include master channel!!
      Parameters:
      masterStack - trigger stack to check
      Returns:
      A java8 stream of pairs. Key is channel identifier and value is channel data. Pairs do not support mutation nor removal. Can still cause ConcurrentModificationException if underlying channel data is modified while stream is working.
